text.Prompt: Can you tell me how to stop safari from filling in the address bar on an iphone?
text.Response A:
Open your iPhone's Settings.
Scroll down and tap Safari.
Slide the "Preload Top Hit" button to the Off position.
text.Response B: Yes, you can disable auto-fill in Safari on your iPhone by going to Settings > Safari > Passwords & AutoFill > AutoFill > Passwords and turning off AutoFill Passwords.

189.displayed_text:
Prompt

Can you tell me how to stop safari from filling in the address bar on an iphone?

Response A

Open your iPhone's Settings.
Scroll down and tap Safari.
Slide the "Preload Top Hit" button to the Off position.

Response B

Yes, you can disable auto-fill in Safari on your iPhone by going to Settings > Safari > Passwords & AutoFill > AutoFill > Passwords and turning off AutoFill Passwords.
